			<pubDate>Wed, 07 Mar 2012 06:00:00 PST</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[60 min. from Wed Mar 7 00:00:00 PST 2012 Show - The human brain is made up of two hemispheres; the left and the right.  Each hemisphere is responsible for the opposite side of the body, receiving sensory and motor input from many different sources and processing accordingly.  Integration between the two sides of the brain is crucial in order for the body to function correctly, but with autism and other neurodevelopmental disorders, that important link is often missing or very weak.  This can affect all higher-level brain processes, including language, reading, writing, social interaction, motor skills and more.  In this episode of The Mother Cub Show, host Susan Lynn Perry will interview Larry Polnicky, owner of the Brain Balance Center in Tampa, Florida.  They will discuss the exciting possibilities for children with autism to rehabilitate and form new neural connections through the use of a specific therapy that not only balances the brain, but the overall health and wellbeing of the child.  ]]></description>
			<enclosure url="http://hwcdn.net/t9f2y9d8/cds/wtr_studioa/201151/perry030712.mp3" length="4727310" type="audio/mpeg" />
