			<description><![CDATA[60 min. from Wed Feb 1 00:00:00 PST 2012 Show - There's no denying the connection between imbalances in the gut and brain causing a host of problems for our kids with autism.  With over 70% of the immune system located in the gut, it just makes sense that when the gut is inflamed or unbalanced, the brain will be affected too.  In this episode of The Mother Cub Show, host Susan Lynn Perry will interview Dr. Michael Goldberg about his research and how the autism epidemic cannot be due to a developmental or genetic disorder, but rather a disease process of the immune system.  The good news is...a disease process can be treated.  He believes that most children with autism are fighting a complex immune/ complex viral disorder and that once treated, the kids stand a good chance of recovering.  The second half of the show will feature two additional guests who are strong autism advocates; one with a theme park designed specifically for our special kids and the other with a game that will help your child get involved with family mealtimes.  ]]></description>
