			<pubDate>Wed, 18 Jan 2012 06:00:00 PST</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[60 min. from Wed Jan 18 00:00:00 PST 2012 Show - When a parent decides to change the diet of their child with autism, it can be a very challenging and daunting intervention. But, it can also be one of the most effective ways to help them. It's challenging because many of our kids already have extremely limited diets. In addition, they may have texture or other sensory issues that can make introducing new foods even more complicated. Dietary intervention can be very effective, though, because if done correctly, it can help reduce inflammation, allergies, and bowel issues, while helping the child's digestive system to be able to absorb nutrients more efficiently from their food. On this episode of The Mother Cub Show, host Susan Lynn Perry will interview Ms. Donna Gates, the founder and creator of The Body Ecology Diet. This diet was created initially to eradicate yeast and other fungal infections from an adult's body, but has had the unexpected benefit of helping many children with autism become healthier as well.]]></description>
