			<description><![CDATA[60 min. from Wed Dec 28 00:00:00 PST 2011 Show - Integrated Listening Systems (ILs) is a therapy originally developed for children and adults with attention issues, but was quickly found to provide substantial benefits for children with autism as well.  In this episode of The Mother Cub Show, host Susan Lynn Perry will interview Dr. Ron Minson, one of the driving forces behind the creation of ILS.  Dr. Minson will discuss how this unique multi-sensory program was the first of its kind, building upon the groundbreaking research of listening therapy pioneer - Dr. Alfred Tomatis.   By combining movement, listening and visual stimulation all within one therapy, the ILS program helps to integrate all sensory systems within the body.  In the second half of the show, a very special lady, named Rebecca Goniwich, will discuss how this particular therapy provided dramatic results for her entire family.  Tune in Wednesday, May 11th, at 8am Pacific on WorldTalk Radio to hear more about this amazing music and movement program.]]></description>
